        <briefdescription>
<para>This function is used to read the state of the shutdown manager. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_dfxasm" kindref="compound">XDfxasm</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns shutdown manager state and its bit significance is as follows. -BIT0 - 0 Entry to Pass Through mode has been requested<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>1 Entry to Shutdown mode has been requested -BIT1 - 0 The read or the write channel (or both) are in the Pass Through mode</para></listitem><listitem><para>1 Both the read and write channels are in the Shutdown Mode -BIT2 - 0 The write channel is in the Pass Through mode</para></listitem><listitem><para>1 The write channel is in the Shutdown Mode -BIT3 - 0 The read channel is in the Pass Through mode</para></listitem><listitem><para>1 The read channel is in the Shutdown Mode</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
